The paper discusses a model for classification of sequence data using Restricted Boltzmann Machines (RBMs) and Recurrent Neural Networks (RNNs). RBMs are a type of generative model commonly used in machine learning, while RNNs are a type of neural network specifically designed for processing sequential data. Therefore, the paper is likely to be relevant to several sub-categories of computer science, including machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), neural networks (cs.NE), natural language processing (cs.CL), and computer vision (cs.CV). Among these, cs.LG is the most likely sub-category as the paper focuses on developing a new model for classification using RBMs and RNNs.
